data.description: Back on the market due to buyer’s financing falling through.    Experience the peace and tranquility of living in the gated community of Grenelefe Country Club. This well-maintained townhome features 2 master bedrooms and 2.5 bathrooms and is surrounded by beautiful green areas, mature trees, and plenty of private space for outdoor enjoyment.    Throughout the house, you'll find stunning views from various vantage points. As you enter the property, you'll notice the natural touches inside, including wooden floors and handrails, as well as numerous details made from the same material. The cozy and well-lit foyer gives you the option to access the two master bedrooms on the first level or take the stairs to discover the expansive living room with vaulted ceilings. The first level includes a dining area, wet bar, kitchen, and a beautiful sunroom with spectacular views this area can be use as a lounge, library, gym, play area, and more. Additionally, you’ll also find stairs that would lead you up to a spacious loft that could be use as and office, mediation room or even like a guest/ day room — the possibilities are endless.    The current owners have made significant upgrades to the kitchen in 2022, including all-new appliances, sink, and new laminate countertops. The roof was replaced in 2020, and in 2021 a new air handler and booster unit were installed for the bonus loft area. Further improvements in 2022 included a new water heater and an entire plumbing replacement in the kitchen. In 2023, both the panel and electrical wiring were updated, a new well pump was installed, and a new screen porch was also installed. Additionally, a smart thermostat was added, and the external part of the chimney was reinforced to withstand storms and hurricanes.    This property is conveniently located near I-4, providing quick access to theme parks, renowned golf courses, shopping malls, restaurants, and much more.      Don’t wait any longer to schedule your showing and make this property your future home! The current owner has put a lot of love and care into this house, her family is growing and ready to upgrade their home.
